HEADWORD: Pensile
<hw>Pen"sile</hw> <pr>(p⟦ecr⟧n"s⟦icr⟧l; 277)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[L. <ets>pensilis</ets>, fr. <ets>pendere</ets> to hang: cf. OE.
<ets>pensil</ets>. See <er>Pendant</er>.]</ety> <def>Hanging; suspended;
pendent; pendulous.</def> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The long, <qex>pensile</qex> branches of the birches.</q>
<rj><qau>W. Howitt.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pensileness</ent>⟦br⟧
